      <h2>Help when water shows up but the source is not obvious</h2>
      <p>Some leaks are easy to see. Others show up as stains, bubbling paint, soft flooring, cabinet damage, moldy smell, or a water meter that moves when fixtures are off. The first step is narrowing down whether the leak is from a fixture, pipe, drain, water heater, shutoff valve, or hidden supply line.</p>
      <p>Fateh Plumbing & Electric helps with hidden leaks, pipe leak repair, ceiling water stains, leaking fixtures, water heater leaks, damp walls, running meters, and active water leaks across Brampton and nearby GTA communities.</p>
      <p>If water is actively leaking, shut off the nearest valve or main water supply if safe. If water is near electrical equipment, avoid the area and call for emergency plumbing support.</p>
    </div>
