      <article><strong>Damp wall or soft flooring</strong><p>Moisture behind drywall, under flooring, or inside cabinets may point to a hidden pipe or fixture leak.</p><a href="pipe-repair.html">Pipe repair</a></article>
      <article><strong>Water meter keeps moving</strong><p>If no fixtures are running but the meter moves, there may be a hidden leak in the plumbing system.</p><a href="contact.html">Request leak check</a></article>
      <article><strong>Water heater area is wet</strong><p>Leaks near a water heater can come from the tank, valve, drain pan, pipe connection, or nearby line.</p><a href="water-heater-repair.html">Water heater repair</a></article>
