    <details><summary>Do you provide leak detection in Brampton?</summary><p>Yes. Fateh Plumbing & Electric provides leak detection in Brampton for visible leaks, hidden pipe leaks, ceiling stains, damp walls, running water meters, and fixture leaks.</p></details>
    <details><summary>When is a water leak an emergency?</summary><p>A water leak can be urgent if water is spreading, dripping through a ceiling, near electrical equipment, damaging finished areas, or cannot be stopped with a shutoff valve. For those situations, call the <a href="emergency-plumber.html">emergency plumber</a> line.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How do I know if I have a hidden plumbing leak?</summary><p>Common signs include ceiling stains, damp drywall, soft flooring, moldy odor, a water meter moving when fixtures are off, unexplained water bills, or sound of running water.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Can the leak be repaired after it is found?</summary><p>Yes. Depending on the source, the repair may connect to <a href="pipe-repair.html">pipe repair</a>, fixture repair, valve replacement, water heater service, or emergency stabilization.</p></details>
